{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014bHfGidKoSayPrwk9ZLNrW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/// Coin sides\n     2→pub const SIDE_HEADS: u8 = 0;\n     3→pub const SIDE_TAILS: u8 = 1;\n     4→\n     5→/// Match phases\n     6→pub const PHASE_WAITING: u8 = 0;   // Creator placed bet, waiting for opponent\n     7→pub const PHASE_LOCKED: u8 = 1;    // Both players in, requesting VRF\n     8→pub const PHASE_SETTLED: u8 = 2;   // VRF resolved, winner determined\n     9→pub const PHASE_CANCELLED: u8 = 3; // Creator cancelled before opponent joined\n    10→\n    11→/// Timeout (in seconds) after which a LOCKED match can be cancelled.\n    12→pub const LOCK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS: i64 = 120; // 2 minutes\n    13→\n    14→/// Derive a coin side (0 or 1) from a randomness byte.\n    15→pub fn from_randomness(byte: u8) -> u8 {\n    16→    byte % 2\n    17→}\n    18→\n    19→/// Returns true if the given value is a valid side (HEADS or TAILS).\n    20→pub fn is_valid_side(side: u8) -> bool {\n    21→    side == SIDE_HEADS || side == SIDE_TAILS\n    22→}\n    23→\n    24→#[cfg(test)]\n    25→mod tests {\n    26→    use super::*;\n    27→\n    28→    #[test]\n    29→    fn test_from_randomness() {\n    30→        assert_eq!(from_randomness(0), SIDE_HEADS);\n    31→        assert_eq!(from_randomness(1), SIDE_TAILS);\n    32→        assert_eq!(from_randomness(2), SIDE_HEADS);\n    33→        assert_eq!(from_randomness(255), SIDE_TAILS);\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    #[test]\n    37→    fn test_is_valid_side() {\n    38→        assert!(is_valid_side(SIDE_HEADS));\n    39→        assert!(is_valid_side(SIDE_TAILS));\n    40→        assert!(!is_valid_side(2));\n    41→        assert!(!is_valid_side(255));\n    42→    }\n    43→}\n    44→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016VAmotY9TiSf2XjJBYHREA","session_id":"78853bc0-87e2-4084-ac9d-e40a4ee398e1","uuid":"4b0d9f96-315b-4b15-a60c-6f9fd2716d43"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016VAmotY9TiSf2XjJBYHREA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've found all the information you requested. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Shared VRF Orao Module\n\n### File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/vrf_orao.rs`\n\n#### `read_orao_randomness` Function (Real Mode)\n```rust\n#[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-vrf\"))]\npub fn read_orao_randomness(randomness_account: &AccountInfo) -> Result<[u8; 32]> {\n    use anchor_lang::AccountDeserialize;\n\n    let data = randomness_account.try_borrow_data()?;\n    let mut buf: &[u8] = &data;\n    let account_data =\n        orao_solana_vrf::state::RandomnessAccountData::try_deserialize_unchecked(&mut buf)?;\n\n    match account_data.fulfilled_randomness() {\n        Some(randomness_64) => {\n            let mut result = [0u8; 32];\n            result.copy_from_slice(&randomness_64[..32]);\n            Ok(result)\n        }\n        None => Err(error!(VrfError::RandomnessNotFulfilled)),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Details:**\n- Deserializes the Orao `RandomnessAccountData` from the account's raw bytes\n- Extracts the first 32 bytes from the 64-byte randomness (via `fulfilled_randomness()`)\n- Returns `RandomnessNotFulfilled` error if the account's `fulfilled_randomness()` returns `None`\n\n#### `is_fulfilled` Function\n```rust\npub fn is_fulfilled(randomness: &[u8; 32]) -> bool {\n    randomness.iter().any(|&b| b != 0)\n}\n```\n\n**Key Details:**\n- Returns `true` if ANY byte in the 32-byte randomness is non-zero\n- Returns `false` if all bytes are zero (not yet fulfilled)\n\n#### `from_randomness` Function\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/constants.rs`\n\n```rust\npub fn from_randomness(byte: u8) -> u8 {\n    byte % 2\n}\n```\n\n**Key Details:**\n- Takes a single byte from the randomness\n- Returns 0 (HEADS) or 1 (TAILS) via modulo 2 operation\n- Ensures deterministic coin side mapping from randomness\n\n---\n\n## Anchor Version\n\n### `@coral-xyz/anchor` Version: **0.32.1**\n\n**In both package.json files:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/package.json` line 18:\n  ```json\n  \"@coral-xyz/anchor\": \"^0.32.1\",\n  ```\n\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/package.json` line 18:\n  ```json\n  \"@coral-xyz/anchor\": \"^0.32.1\",\n  ```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Account Layout & Flow\n\n1. **Account Layout:** The Orao account is accessed via `orao_solana_vrf::state::RandomnessAccountData`\n2. **Randomness Bytes:** Stored as 64 bytes internally; we extract the first 32 bytes\n3. **Fulfillment Check:** Call `fulfilled_randomness()` — returns `Some(randomness_64)` if fulfilled, `None` otherwise\n4. **Coin Derivation:** Pass any byte from the 32-byte randomness to `from_randomness()` to get 0 or 1"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a76b1bb590de69991 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 32186\ntool_uses: 5\nduration_ms: 22255</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78853bc0-87e2-4084-ac9d-e40a4ee398e1","uuid":"06c0aa91-a93a-421f-a2da-e5c308ccea1f","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read these files to help me understand:\n\n1. The shared VRF orao module - search for `vrf_orao` in `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/` — I need to understand how randomness is read from the Orao account (the account layout, what offset the randomness bytes are at, how \"fulfilled\" is determined)\n\n2. Check the `@coral-xyz/anchor` version in `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/package.json` and `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/package.json`\n\n3. Check `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/constants.rs` for the `from_randomness` function\n\nReturn the exact code for:\n- `read_orao_randomness` function or however randomness bytes are extracted\n- `is_fulfilled` function for Orao accounts\n- `from_