in side mapping from randomness\n\n---\n\n## Anchor Version\n\n### `@coral-xyz/anchor` Version: **0.32.1**\n\n**In both package.json files:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/package.json` line 18:\n  ```json\n  \"@coral-xyz/anchor\": \"^0.32.1\",\n  ```\n\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/package.json` line 18:\n  ```json\n  \"@coral-xyz/anchor\": \"^0.32.1\",\n  ```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Account Layout & Flow\n\n1. **Account Layout:** The Orao account is accessed via `orao_solana_vrf::state::RandomnessAccountData`\n2. **Randomness Bytes:** Stored as 64 bytes internally; we extract the first 32 bytes\n3. **Fulfillment Check:** Call `fulfilled_randomness()` — returns `Some(randomness_64)` if fulfilled, `None` otherwise\n4. **Coin Derivation:** Pass any byte from the 32-byte randomness to `from_randomness()` to get 0 or 1"}],"totalDurationMs":22255,"totalTokens":32186,"totalToolUseCount":5,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3906,"cache_read_input_tokens":27355,"output_tokens":918,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3906,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016DfGcYRTpvPFdDEWvdysbp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the context. Let me write the verification utility.\n\nKey points:\n1. Anchor 0.32.1 — `EventParser` in this version uses generator-based API: `eventParser.parseLogs(logs)` returns a generator\n2. The Orao randomness account uses `orao_solana_vrf::state::RandomnessAccountData` — from TypeScript, I need to check the account data directly. The `fulfilled_randomness()` method returns 64 bytes when fulfilled (first 32 bytes are used). If not fulfilled, it returns None.\n3. For checking fulfillment from TypeScript: The account data is a Borsh-serialized struct. \n\nFor the Orao VRF account from TypeScript, I'll fetch the account info and check for non-zero bytes in the randomness portion of the Borsh-serialized data, accounting for the 8-byte Anchor discriminator at the start of the struct. Writing the TypeScript code...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5620,"cache_read_input_tokens":61456,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5620},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78853bc0-87e2-4084-ac9d-e40a4ee398e1","uuid":"918dc675-5496-497f-967b-0ee457630d2d"}
